{"info":{"author":"Tommaso De Rossi","author_email":"daer.tommy@gmail.com","bugtrack_url":null,"classifiers":["Intended Audience :: Information Technology","Programming Language :: Python :: 3","Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6","Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"],"description":"# compose-watcher\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/remorses/compose-watcher/master/.github/compose_watcher_video.gif'>\n</p>\n\nCli that restarts you docker compose services when a file inside one of its volumes changes\nTo use with compiled languages place the compilation step in the `command` field.\n\nExample usage\n\n-   graphql api restart when schema file changes\n-   [Mongoke](https://github.com/remorses/mongoke) restarts when config schema changes\n-   Nodejs container restarts when the src folder changes, recompiling with tsc\n\n## Install\n\n```\npip3 install compose-watcher\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nUse the directories you want to track as service volumes\nAlso consider using `init: true` in the compose service definition for faster killing of processes.\nTo not stop the `docker-compose logs` command, there should be always a running container\n\n```\nversion: '3'\n\nservices:\n  api:\n    build: node_api\n    command: sh -c 'tsc --incremental && node index.js'\n    volumes:\n      - ./node_api/src:/src\n\n```\n\nThen execute `compose-watcher` to watch changes\n\n```\ncompose-watcher -f docker-compose.yml --timeout 5\n```\n\nTODO add extension filter\nTODO add services names as positional arguments\nTODO dont block the event receiving thread when restarting","description_content_type":"text/markdown","docs_url":null,"download_url":"","downloads":{"last_day":-1,"last_month":-1,"last_week":-1},"home_page":"https://github.com/remorses/compose-watcher","keywords":"docker-compose,watcher,watch","license":"Apache Software License 2.0","maintainer":"","maintainer_email":"","name":"compose-watcher","package_url":"https://pypi.org/project/compose-watcher/","platform":"","project_url":"https://pypi.org/project/compose-watcher/","project_urls":{"Homepage":"https://github.com/remorses/compose-watcher"},"release_url":"https://pypi.org/project/compose-watcher/1.1.5/","requires_dist":null,"requires_python":"","summary":"compose-watcher","version":"1.1.5"},"last_serial":6811520,"releases":{"1.0.1":[{"comment_text":"","digests":{"md5":"6ad6426b9b334430be029e0004dcca81","sha256":"e737055d0662385b13040646da1bd67aa0dbb2302f2dc7f5a7aa7bc485e4c241"},"downloads":-1,"filename":"compose-watcher-1.0.1.tar.gz","has_sig":false,"md5_digest":"6ad6426b9b334430be029e0004dcca81","packagetype":"sdist","python_version":"source","requires_python":null,"size":3970,"upload_time":"2020-03-14T12:25:40","upload_time_iso_8601":"2020-03-14T12:25:40.982188Z","url":"https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/fc/6c/8ed2818a77abd31b2f5d95da764c93341c75f588b8c7fd3fd9017d661523/compose-watcher-1.0.1.tar.gz"}],"1.0.2":[{"comment_text":"","digests":{"md5":"a6d9c097c88a2b6cdf5c02c0b68f77a6","sha256":"5572e90884280e30d43a5d074b9ceff3bc9f2f05220c756e762cea24d09219f1"},"downloads":-1,"filename":"compose-watcher-1.0.2.tar.gz","has_sig":false,"md5_digest":"a6d9c097c88a2b6cdf5c02c0b68f77a6","packagetype":"sdist","python_version":"source","requires_python":null,"size":4031,"upload_time":"2020-03-14T12:38:10","upload_time_iso_8601":"2020-03-14T12:38:10.729601Z","url":"https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/ce/5e/d4277acfc09feaaa641812c5734c4deff19b4a068d3e13775c381944c03b/compose-watcher-1.0.2.tar.gz"}],"1.1.1":[{"comment_text":"","digests":{"md5":"0c69c44ddad7ab84976c39740db8fed6","sha256":"d0b51ba6344242b435dafd6282d2b2da1b5811c62b683aec2b33b9071881509a"},"downloads":-1,"filename":"compose-watcher-1.1.1.tar.gz","has_sig":false,"md5_digest":"0c69c44ddad7ab84976c39740db8fed6","packagetype":"sdist","python_version":"source","requires_python":null,"size":4364,"upload_time":"2020-03-14T13:13:44","upload_time_iso_8601":"2020-03-14T13:13:44.592236Z","url":"https:/